				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Test server with testbuf is a great idea.  
<br />

<br />
Now on making a mage or not. 
<br />

<br />
 If you are serious about playing EQ and have goals like i want to see eplanes and time then i would say NO.
<br />

<br />
If you plan on just having fun but somewhere inside you there is a sinking feeling you want to do more join a guild and progess, then i would say NO.
<br />

<br />
So if all you want to do is level and not think about what other classes are doing then a mage is for you.  But you have to remember once you hit 65 what are u going to do?  A mage at 65 with all his spells are limited in my opinion where other classes are not as limit ie chanter, necro, wizzie, or bard.  EQ has become a game for DPS, CC, clerics, and warriors with afew utility classes thrown in there.  If you want to progess in the game to Eplanes or high then pick another class then mage plain and simple.  Caster class i would go wizzie for pure DPS, chanter cause they rule <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="Smile" border="0" />, or necro( a good necro is awesome to watch) oh yeah DRUID too.  Melee class rogue or ranger for DPS.
<br />

<br />
If sony came to me right now and say we will exchange Aadr for any class you want same level and AA i would change in a heartbeat.  I would never look back either.  Now what class would i choice?  hmm that would be the tough one.  I really enjoy rogue and ranger.  But man a wizzie would be sweet.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
