			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I've been playing since the day of commercial release, somewhere in 1999 and I've played a little of everything.  No matter what class I've played, once I got to the high end into raiding and such, I've hated every one of my classes.  However, in groups, its a different story.  You'll hear thousands of stories about how badly class_X sucks, but in the end, it's up to you.  Getting someone else to tell you what class to play is like asking someone about what your sexual preference should be.  If I were starting over again with no idea of what to play, I'd go to the various class web sites and get some info on each, then fo to the test server and try them all out.  See for yourself which you like best, then go for it.  Too many people 'waste' huge amounts of time grinding in a class because they feel attached to the character and end up disliking the class (clerics and warriors for my own part).  At 65, noone sucks.  You're either happy or you're not and you pay to be happy.<br />_________________<br /><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=344604">Arriann Val'Sharess</A> 
<br />
65 Arch-Convoker
<br />
Tholuxe Paells
