			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">If your going to solo the majority of time I'd say play a Necromancer. My heart belongs to my Mage, but having raised a Necro alt to 54 I can say that the life of the dark priest is less frustrating than that of the summoner. Much of that has to do with other classes not understanding Mages and also the fact that necro mana regen is second to none. The utility of the necro class is also very impressive. 
<br />

<br />
If your going to do 50/50 solo group I'd vote Druid as they bring utility and can solo quite well if no groups are available. A Mage would be my second choice as a 50/50 player, yes you can do quite well up to about 50 or so but you may see that finding groups is harder.
<br />

<br />
I'm not and never will be a "uber geared" or "hard core raider" so I can't really comment of that part of the high end game. At the end of the day it all boils down to having fun.
<br />

<br />
Shamans get tired of slowing and trying to lose aggro
<br />
Wizzies get tired of "sit n med, nuke, repeat"
<br />
