</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
* regarding expansions, stick with Evolutions only until you decide you like your class.  At around level 28-32 go for LDON.  Don't worry about GoD at all, you will know when you finally need it.
<br />

<br />
* regarding class.  I recommend playing around and reading a lot.  Mages are really fun.  I love my mage and when I started (just 5 months ago) I played a mage as one of my first three test characters.
<br />

<br />
I think the testbuff thing is ok but get familiar with the geography of Norrath first.  Learn the zones and levels to play them.  In the beginning a melee type is very exciting as you can get in a fight or ambushed and actually survive.  A mage, wizard or necro who is ambushed and unprepared would just fold and die or run run run.  This might be frustrating but if you get set up right a wizard, mage, or necro can rock.  
<br />

<br />
Good luck and enjoy EQ.  It really is an awesome game.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
