				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Well now that they are starting to work a bit on pets I'd say give it a shot for a bit.  Keep in mind though in the long run 51 to 65 is really screwy as a side effect of the exspasions were made.  Its up and down and left and right on the power scale for the mage and alot of other classes.  
<br />

<br />
If your looking to have fun mage isn't to bad now days.  If your looking to do great things and kill big mobs I'd say not to get to deep into EQ as EQ2 and WoW along with a few others are coming soon.  It's just my instincts here but I'm figure the brave, bold, and extremely deciated types that are needed for super hi end raiding are pulling out soon to take it the "next level" of raiding.  Just my call though EQ could and quite possibily outlive EQ2 and WoW if the devs for EQ 1 are on top of things.  As it is GoD making things for the long run look not so good.
