			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">They really have no weakness.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
IMHO Necros do have one major weakness: inability to do damage rapidly and efficiently in a typical XP group (though my Necro is only level 60, so neurotoxin may improve that at 61). Necro nukes are relatively low on damage, generally inefficient on mana and resisted even more than Mage nukes, and few DoTs do enough damage fast enough to make up for the mana cost: the only real compensating factor is the fast mana regen from the Lich spells.
<br />

<br />
Sure, if they don't have a chanter I can mez mobs up to 55 or aggro kite others, if they don't have a slower I can slow undead, etc, etc, but I'm not terribly efficient in a pure DPS role if they do have all those other slots filled.
<br />

<br />
Plus, of course, Necros can't summon beer and fireworks.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
